a\";s:24:\"what causes orphan pages\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=142465\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:430:\"<p>Are you looking for an easy way to find and fix orphan pages in WordPress? Orphan pages can hurt your SEO and rob you of traffic. In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn a simple way to find and fix orphan pages&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-orphan-pages-in-wordpress/\">How to Easily Find and Fix Orphan Pages in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32350:\"<p>Are you looking for an easy way to find and fix orphan pages in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Orphan pages can hurt your SEO and rob you of traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn a simple way to find and fix orphan pages in WordPress, so your rankings in search results don’t suffer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What you&#8217;ll need</strong>: The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing\" title=\"\">All in One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) plugin</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-2 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-are-orphan-pages\">What are Orphan Pages?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-find-orphan-pages\">Step 2: Find Orphan Pages</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-3-how-to-fix-orphan-pages-and-posts\">Step 3: Fix Orphan Pages</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-beware-more-is-not-always-better\">Beware: More is Not Always Better</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-are-orphan-pages-bad-for-seo\">Why are Orphan Pages Bad for SEO?</a><ul></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-are-orphan-pages\">What are Orphan Pages?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Orphan pages are website pages that have no inbound links from other pages on your site. Because of this, they&#8217;re hard for users and search engines to find. As a result, &#8220;orphans&#8221; may get little or no traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s fine if the orphan page is a test page that you simply forgot about. But if it&#8217;s a page with content you care about, you&#8217;ll need to fix it so people can find it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But don&#8217;t worry: there&#8217;s an easy way to find and fix orphan pages in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First, we recommend you <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">install and activate AIOSEO</a>. (Currently, over 3 million people are using this plugin and a majority of reviewers on WordPress.org have given it 5 stars.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO has a nifty <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-link-assistant-to-optimize-your-internal-linking-strategy/\"><strong>Link Assistant</strong></a> tool that makes it easy to find and fix orphan pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png\" alt=\"aioseo homepage\" class=\"wp-image-140989\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage.png 1260w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve downloaded the zip file of the plugin, open your WordPress editor. Go to <strong>Plugins » Add New</strong> and upload the file.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A simple multi-step wizard will open and walk you through the setup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, go to <strong>AIOSEO » Feature Manager</strong> and toggle the <strong>Link Assistant</strong> feature to “Activated.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"639\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-1024x639.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142483\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-1024x639.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-300x187.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-768x479.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-600x374.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-96x60.png 96w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant-144x90.png 144w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/activate-aioseo-link-assistant.png 1441w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-2-find-orphan-pages\">Step 2: Find Orphan Pages</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, in the left-hand column of your WordPress editor, go to <strong>AIOSEO » Link Assistant.</strong> This will open the Link Assistant dashboard. Then click on <strong>Orphaned Posts.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"587\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-1024x587.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142484\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-1024x587.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-300x172.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-768x440.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-600x344.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-105x60.png 105w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1-157x90.png 157w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1.png 1247w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you can see a list of all your orphaned web pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, these are listed chronologically, with the most recent orphaned page at the top.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"630\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-1024x630.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142485\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-1024x630.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-300x184.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-768x472.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-600x369.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-98x60.png 98w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list-146x90.png 146w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-orphan-link-list.png 1207w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the left is the <strong>Post Title</strong> followed by the <strong>Publish Date</strong> and some other columns.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The <strong>Internal</strong> column displays the number of inbound internal links (at left) and number of outbound internal links (right.) As you may have expected, all the orphaned posts display &#8220;0&#8221; inbound internal links.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"515\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-1024x515.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142486\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-1024x515.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-300x151.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-768x387.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-600x302.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-119x60.png 119w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links-179x90.png 179w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/orphaned-posts-no-internal-links.png 1212w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The <strong>Suggestions</strong> column displays a number next to a link icon. This number is the total number of suggestions that Link Assistant has for you to view.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"312\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-1024x312.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142487\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-1024x312.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-300x92.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-768x234.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-600x183.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-190x58.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column-295x90.png 295w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-suggestions-column.png 1213w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To fix these orphaned posts, we&#8217;ll be using that <strong>Suggestions </strong>column.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Note: The number of <strong>Suggestions</strong> will vary depending on the amount and type of content on your site.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-step-3-how-to-fix-orphan-pages-and-posts\">Step 3: How to Fix Orphan Pages and Posts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, to fix orphan posts, you&#8217;ll be adding one or more links <em>from other articles</em> on your site <em>to</em> the orphaned post. These are called &#8220;internal links.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For our tutorial, we&#8217;ll be fixing an orphan page called &#8220;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-emojis-to-your-wordpress-blog/\" title=\"\">How to Add Emojis to Your WordPress Blog</a>.&#8221; (We’ll refer to this as our “Emoji article” for short.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-view-the-internal-link-suggestions\">View the Internal Link Suggestions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let&#8217;s look at the link <strong>Suggestions</strong>. To do this, click on the <strong>Post Title</strong> or click on the link icon next to the Suggestions number. This will reveal the link suggestions.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"265\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-1024x265.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142488\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-1024x265.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-300x78.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-768x198.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-600x155.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-190x49.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions-348x90.png 348w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-find-orphan-link-suggestions.png 1316w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the example below, we clicked on our emoji article title and found several suggestions including these two:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"322\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-1024x322.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142531\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-1024x322.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-300x94.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-768x242.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-600x189.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-190x60.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions-286x90.png 286w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-orphan-link-suggestions.png 1255w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>In the <strong>left-hand column</strong> above you see the name of an article that Link Assistant suggests we link <em>from</em>.</li><li>In the <strong>right-hand column</strong>, the Assistant has suggested we link from one of two phrases. And it’s suggested the exact anchor text in this post that the link be added to. (The blue “add emojis” link goes to our orphan emoji article.)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Notice that Link Assistant is choosing text that&#8217;s <em>relevant</em> to our emoji article.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-add-a-link-to-an-orphan-page\">How to Add a Link to an Orphan Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you like a link Suggestion, click the <strong>Add Link</strong> button at the right. This will automatically add the link for you. (You don&#8217;t even have to open the post!)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"389\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-1024x389.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142489\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-1024x389.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-300x114.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-768x292.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-600x228.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-158x60.png 158w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages-237x90.png 237w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-fix-orpan-pages.png 1283w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-change-the-suggested-anchor-text\">How to Change the Suggested Anchor Text</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>What if you want to add the suggested link, but you want to choose different anchor text?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To choose different anchor text, hover your cursor over the suggested text and click the pencil icon that appears. A small editing window will open.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"444\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-1024x444.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142533\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-1024x444.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-300x130.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-768x333.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-600x260.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-138x60.png 138w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link-208x90.png 208w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-alter-anchor-text-for-orphan-link.png 1255w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Use your cursor to highlight the word or phrase that you want the link to appear on.</li><li>Then click the link icon above the window. The link will be applied to the text you highlighted.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"959\" height=\"542\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142534\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text.png 959w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text-300x170.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text-768x434.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text-600x339.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text-106x60.png 106w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-change-anchor-text-159x90.png 159w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you know how to find and fix orphan pages with <strong>Link Assistant</strong> and how to change the suggested anchor text.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That was easy, wasn&#8217;t it?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-beware-more-is-not-always-better\">Beware: More is Not Always Better</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Orphan links are kind of like vitamins: just because they&#8217;re good for you and easy to use, doesn&#8217;t mean more is better! Taking too many vitamins can be bad for your health, and adding too many links to orphan pages can be bad for SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s why: search engines use <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-wordpress-internal-links-to-improve-your-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">internal links</a> to understand your site structure. They want to know which articles are related, topic-wise, and what are the most important pages on your site. This information helps search engines match pages to search queries.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Typically, your most important pages have the greatest number of inbound links. So imagine you added 50 internal links to every single page on your site. This makes it harder for Google to figure out which articles are on related topics and which pages are the most important.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Too many links on a page can also make the text hard for users to read, as you can see in the example below.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"177\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-1024x177.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142536\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-1024x177.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-300x52.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-768x133.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-600x104.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-190x33.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks-520x90.png 520w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/example-too-many-hyperlinks.png 1243w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a rule of thumb to follow. Always do what you think is best for the reader. Consider what related articles might genuinely be helpful or interesting to them. And do this while keeping in mind your overall site goals, such as growing revenue and subscribers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-dealing-with-unwanted-orphan-pages\">Dealing With Unwanted Orphan Pages</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>So far we&#8217;ve discussed how to fix orphan content pages. But what if you have some orphan pages that you don&#8217;t want to keep? These might be:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Test pages</li><li>Defunct product pages</li><li>Underperforming pages</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-test-pages\">Test Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can simply delete these. However, if there is traffic coming to the page we suggest you use AIOSEO’s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/adding-a-redirect-when-you-delete-content/\"><strong>Redirection Manager</strong></a><strong>. </strong>Whenever you delete a page or post, it will ask you where you want that URL to be redirected to.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-defunct-product-pages\">Defunct Product Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Products that you no longer sell should not be listed on your site. To clean these up, use the AIOSEO <strong>Redirection Manager</strong> to redirect the URL to a similar product or your storefront and delete the defunct page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-underperforming-pages\">Underperforming Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have some orphan pages with weak content that you want to delete. Consider whether the content can be improved and combined with another page. If so, then use the AIOSEO Redirection Manager once you&#8217;re ready to delete the orphan page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Otherwise, simply delete it and follow the instructions above for test pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-orphaned-by-design-ppc-landing-pages\">Orphaned by Design: PPC Landing Pages</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Bear in mind that some website pages are intentionally created to be orphans. For example, PPC (pay-per-click advertising) <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/how-to-create-a-simple-landing-page/\">landing pages</a> or social media campaign pages are often created with no navigational links. (The reason for this is to encourage visitors to stay on the promotional page until they convert.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this case, the pages may not be designed to attract organic traffic (i.e., free traffic) from search engine results pages (SERPs). Instead, they may be focused solely on paid traffic (traffic coming from ads). (If you don&#8217;t want these pages in search results, consider adding the &#8220;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/showing-or-hiding-your-content-in-search-results/\">noindex</a>&#8221; attribute to them so they&#8217;ll remain invisible to search engines.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-are-there-other-ways-to-fix-orphan-pages\">Are There Other Ways to Fix Orphan Pages?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve seen how Link Assistant saves time and is simple enough to be used by beginners with no SEO or technical knowledge. You may be wondering if there are other ways to find and fix orphan pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, there are. Be aware that some of the online how-tos on this topic are complicated and aimed at web professionals. For example, one of the best articles on the subject suggests using multiple digital tools and assets including ahrefs, Google Analytics, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-verify-your-site-with-google-search-console/\" title=\"\">Google Search Console</a>, spreadsheets, array formulas, server log files, and more!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, with Link Assistant, you don&#8217;t have to find orphans or find relevant pages to link from. It&#8217;s all done for you. All you have to do is click a button or two.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-are-orphan-pages-bad-for-seo\">Why are Orphan Pages Bad for SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Orphan pages are bad for SEO for several reasons. They may not show up in any searches at all. This is because search engine crawlers (also called &#8220;spiders&#8221; or &#8220;bots&#8221;) use existing links to find and “index&#8221; (or &#8220;catalog&#8221;) new content. They crawl links on your site and backlinks. (Backlinks are links from other websites to yours.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because orphan pages are disconnected from other pages on the internet, they can be invisible to search engines or their discovery may be delayed. This is true even if the orphan page is included in an <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-an-xml-sitemap/#video\">XML sitemap</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Even if crawlers do find the orphans, those pages won&#8217;t have the page views or SEO value that can come from inbound links. What kind of value? Well-chosen (and well-placed) links convey context, helping search engines understand the relative importance of the page and where it sits in your overall site structure. These links also pass what&#8217;s called &#8220;<a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-wordpress-internal-links-to-improve-your-seo/#juice\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">link juice</a>&#8221; (a type of reputation score) to the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-link-juice-and-orphan-pages-lets-get-the-party-started\">Link Juice and Orphan Pages: Let&#8217;s Get the Party Started</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To understand &#8220;link juice&#8221; or link equity, imagine that you&#8217;ve arrived at a party where you don&#8217;t know anyone. Because the partygoers don&#8217;t have any prior connection to you, they don&#8217;t notice you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now imagine you arrive at the same party, but with someone well-known and liked by the partiers. Suddenly, they know something about you: you&#8217;re connected to their friend and they assume you&#8217;re likable and trustworthy too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your friend&#8217;s reputation has benefited you. Similarly, an orphan page benefits when another page adds a link to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-poor-user-experience\">Poor User Experience</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If site visitors do find an orphan page via your search function, they would have to copy and save the URL somewhere if they wanted to return to the page. This is inconvenient.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And while having some orphan pages is common for sites, too many orphans may signal to users (or search engines) that your site is poorly maintained or has been abandoned. This is particularly true if your e-commerce site has product pages that are defunct yet show up in internal searches. And that can hurt <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-optimization-guide/\">conversions and sales</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-bonus-tips\">Bonus Tips</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>New pages are often orphan pages: </strong>This is because most people publish new content without linking to it from existing content. Remember, your most recent orphan pages will display at the top of the AIOSEO Link Assistant&#8217;s <strong>Orphaned Posts</strong> list.</li><li><strong>Create a routine:</strong> Internal linking is part of a good SEO strategy. So why not make a routine of using Link Assistant once a month to check for orphan posts and to find other internal linking opportunities? External links (links to other sites) can boost your SEO too. Find out more in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-guide/\" title=\"\">link-building guide</a>.</li><li><strong>Watch out for site migrations</strong>: Getting a new website? if you’re moving to a new platform (like from Drupal to WordPress), this website migration process can create orphaned content. Be sure your website project manager has a plan to account for every content URL on your site. (This can be done using a specialty tool like Screaming Frog SEO Spider.)</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-technical-questions-related-to-orphan-pages\">Technical Questions Related to Orphan Pages</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The issues below are for site owners at the intermediate or advanced level. Feel free to <a href=\"#aioseo-whats-next\" title=\"\">skip down to our conclusion</a> if these don’t interest you.</p>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-find-orphan-pages-with-ahrefs\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How do I find orphan pages with ahrefs?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>To find orphan pages using an <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">ahrefs account</a>, first, run a site audit. Once your audit is complete, navigate to <strong>Overview » Tools » Page Explorer</strong>. In the<strong> Links</strong> dropdown, select <strong>Orphan Pages </strong>to view a list of orphan URLs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-1024x462.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142538\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-1024x462.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-300x135.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-768x347.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-600x271.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-133x60.png 133w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages-199x90.png 199w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ahrefs-find-orphan-pages.png 1179w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-find-orphan-pages-in-google-analytics\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How do I find orphan pages in Google Analytics?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Google Analytics is often used, in conjunction with other tools, to find orphan pages in large sites. Start by selecting, in the left-hand navigation, <strong>Behavior » Site Content » All Pages</strong>. Select the desired date range then export the list of URLs as a CSV file. Next, you&#8217;ll need to cross-reference that list with an orphan page list generated by a site audit tool, like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Semrush</a> or ahrefs. In this use case, you&#8217;ll be looking for any orphan pages missed by the site audit tool.<br><br>Note: After July 1, 2023, some aspects of Universal Analytics will no longer be available. Google Analytics is encouraging users to go ahead and switch to Google Analytics 4 (GA4). Be aware that the Behavior navigation item is not present in <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-google-analytics-4-to-wordpress-best-way/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GA4</a>.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-do-orphan-pages-impact-crawl-budget\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Do orphan pages impact crawl budget?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Some articles about orphan pages warn that they can waste Google&#8217;s &#8220;crawl budget.&#8221; However, Google says that crawl budget &#8220;is not something most publishers have to worry about&#8221; especially if you only have a few thousand pages on your site. Crawl budget is a technical SEO topic and best suited for advanced webmasters. You can read more about it <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/blog/2017/01/what-crawl-budget-means-for-googlebot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">here</a>.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-is-link-equity-the-same-thing-as-pagerank\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Is link equity the same thing as PageRank?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Some SEO professionals use &#8220;link equity,&#8221; &#8220;link juice,&#8221; and “PageRank&#8221; interchangeably. So let&#8217;s clarify the terms a bit. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>PageRank is an early creation of Google&#8217;s founders, Larry Page and Sergey Brin. It&#8217;s a mathematical ranking formula that takes into account the number and quality of websites linking to yours. (PageRank is cited numerous times in a <a href=\"http://infolab.stanford.edu/~backrub/google.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">paper they published</a> at Stanford when they were PhD candidates.) According to Google, PageRank is still a ranking factor, but it&#8217;s one of hundreds. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Link juice or link equity refers to the sharing or passing of &#8220;authority&#8221; from a high-ranking page to a lower-ranking page.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you understand why fixing orphan pages is important and how easy it can be. You may also want to check out our article on how to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-small-business-seo/\">boost your SEO without expert help</a> and our complete <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-orphan-pages-in-wordpress/\">How to Easily Find and Fix Orphan Pages in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-orphan-pages-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"[New] SEO Preview: More Control Over Search and Social Snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:184:\"https://aioseo.com/new-seo-preview-more-control-over-search-and-social-snippets/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=new-seo-preview-more-control-over-search-and-social-snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://aioseo.com/new-seo-preview-more-control-over-search-and-social-snippets/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 06 Dec 2022 13:30:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"google search snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"seo preview\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"serp snippet preview tool\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"serp snippet tool\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=140304\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:480:\"<p>We’ve just rolled out AIOSEO 4.2.8, and we have some exciting news! Managing your search engine optimization (SEO) has become much easier with our latest feature: SEO Preview. The SEO Preview works in the WordPress admin bar on the front&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/new-seo-preview-more-control-over-search-and-social-snippets/\">[New] SEO Preview: More Control Over Search and Social Snippets</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Benjamin Rojas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8462:\"<p>We’ve just rolled out AIOSEO 4.2.8, and we have some exciting news!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Managing your search engine optimization (SEO) has become much easier with our latest feature: SEO Preview. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SEO Preview works in the WordPress admin bar on the front end (in preview mode) to enable you to quickly get a preview of what that page will look like as a search snippet on Google. It also helps you see how your page’s Facebook and Twitter share snippets will look when shared on the platforms.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SEO Preview also comes with an SEO Inspector that gives you an overview of your basic SEO and meta tags.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All these are designed to help you optimize your content for search and social sharing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a new addition to all the other powerful features you already love in the plugin. To access this new feature, click the AIOSEO menu icon on the WordPress admin bar while in preview mode. You’ll find the SEO Preview option in the menu:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"308\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend.png\" alt=\"The SEO Preview feature can be found in the AIOSEO menu in your admin bar.\" class=\"wp-image-140575\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-300x132.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-600x263.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s dive into what to expect from this dynamic module.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-background-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-drive-engagement-on-serps-by-optimizing-your-google-snippet-preview\">Drive Engagement on SERPs By Optimizing Your Google Snippet Preview</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-optimize-your-social-snippet-for-better-social-media-engagement\">Optimize Your Social Snippet for Better Social Media Engagement</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-ensure-your-page-is-properly-optimized-with-the-seo-inspector\">Ensure Your Page is Properly Optimized With the SEO Inspector</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-drive-engagement-on-serps-by-optimizing-your-google-snippet-preview\">Drive Engagement on SERPs By Optimizing Your Google Snippet Preview&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Google snippet preview is a feature that allows you to see what your page or post will look like on Google’s search engine results pages (SERPs). Elements in the snippet preview include the slug, post title, meta description, and featured image.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"601\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-google-1.png\" alt=\"The Google search preview shows you how your snippets look on SERPs.\" class=\"wp-image-140576\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-google-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-google-1-300x257.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-google-1-600x514.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only do you get a preview of what your search snippet will look like, but you can also edit the snippet to better optimize it for search. All you have to do is click the <strong>Edit Snippet</strong> button, and you’ll be taken to AIOSEO’s meta box, where you can make the desired changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This will help you ensure your snippets are optimized to drive engagement and clicks on SERPs, boosting organic traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-optimize-your-social-snippet-for-better-social-media-engagement\">Optimize Your Social Snippet for Better Social Media Engagement&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Another powerful feature of the SEO Preview module is the Social snippet preview. This is designed to help you see and optimize how your page or post will look when shared on Facebook and Twitter.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"531\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-facebook.png\" alt=\"The Facebook snippet preview shows you how your snippets will look when users share your page.\" class=\"wp-image-140577\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-facebook.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-facebook-300x228.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-facebook-600x455.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As with the Google preview, you can also use this part of the module to edit your social media metadata, like the title, description, image source, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-ensure-your-page-is-properly-optimized-with-the-seo-inspector\">Ensure Your Page is Properly Optimized With the SEO Inspector</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To help ensure your page is well-optimized, the SEO Inspector gives you a quick look at your basic SEO. These are elements like your focus keyphrase, readability, and your title. This helps you see at a glance what you need to improve on. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"550\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-seo-inspector.png\" alt=\"The SEO Inspector gives you an overview of your basic SEO and meta tags.\" class=\"wp-image-140578\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-seo-inspector.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-seo-inspector-300x236.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/seo-preview-frontend-seo-inspector-600x471.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you notice any aspect of your SEO that needs improvement, simply click the <strong>Edit Post</strong> button to make your changes. This will take you back to editor mode so you can implement the changes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SEO Inspector also shows you all the meta tags for that particular page. Meta tags are critical elements of effective SEO as they help prove search intent, improve organic CTR, and boost your SEO. They also help search engines understand your content, resulting in better indexing.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO 4.2.8’s SEO Inspector, you’ll get a comprehensive overview of all the important meta tags on your page. This includes the title, description, Canonical URL, image meta, and Facebook and Twitter tags, among others.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SEO Inspector is a powerful tool that can help ensure you tick all the SEO boxes on each page of your website. As a result, you’ll stand a better chance of ranking high on SERPs and increasing traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides this major update, we’ve made several notable improvements to many features you already love. You can see those in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/changelog/\">full product changelog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Update your site to AIOSEO 4.2.8 to unlock these powerful new features and rank your content higher on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’re not yet using AIOSEO, make sure to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">install and activate the plugin today</a>. Our SEO plugin will help you outrank your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have questions about these features, please comment below or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/contact/\">contact our customer support team</a>. We’re always ready to help.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our commitment to making AIOSEO the easiest and best WordPress SEO plugin is only getting stronger as we continue to win together with our customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re so grateful for your continued support, feedback, and suggestions. Please keep those suggestions and feature requests coming!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you enjoy using these new SEO features as much as we enjoyed creating them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>-Benjamin Rojas (President of AIOSEO).</em></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/new-seo-preview-more-control-over-search-and-social-snippets/\">[New] SEO Preview: More Control Over Search and Social Snippets</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"https://aioseo.com/new-seo-preview-more-control-over-search-and-social-snippets/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"The Beginner’s Guide to WordPress Multilingual SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:162:\"https://aioseo.com/the-beginners-guide-to-wordpress-multilingual-seo/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=the-beginners-guide-to-wordpress-multilingual-seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://aioseo.com/the-beginners-guide-to-wordpress-multilingual-seo/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 01 Dec 2022 19:41:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"beginners guide for wordpress multilingual seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"multilingual plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"translation plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"what is multilingual seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"wordpress multilingual seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=140986\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:475:\"<p>Do you want to learn about WordPress multilingual SEO? WordPress multilingual SEO can help you captivate and grow an international audience that converts. In this tutorial, we’ll show you the easy way to handle the technical part. And we&#8217;ll provide&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/the-beginners-guide-to-wordpress-multilingual-seo/\">The Beginner’s Guide to WordPress Multilingual SEO</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40669:\"<p>Do you want to learn about WordPress multilingual SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress multilingual SEO can help you captivate and grow an international audience that converts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, we’ll show you the easy way to handle the technical part. And we&#8217;ll provide tips for creating content that will help your multilingual WordPress site rank.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What you&#8217;ll need</strong>: The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) plugin and a translation plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-4 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-wordpress-multilingual-seo\">What is WordPress Multilingual SEO?</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-youll-need-an-seo-plugin-and-a-translation-plugin\">You’ll Need an SEO Plugin and a Translation Plugin</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install and Setup the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-install-and-setup-the-wpml-translation-plugin\">Step 2: Install and Setup the WPML Translation Plugin</a><ul></ul></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-wordpress-multilingual-seo-foundations\">WordPress Multilingual SEO Foundations</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-optimizing-content-for-multilingual-seo\">Optimizing Content for Multilingual SEO</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-link-building-a-powerful-seo-tactic\">Link-Building: A Powerful SEO Tactic</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-bonus-tips-for-growing-your-multilingual-wordpress-site\">Bonus Tips for Growing Your Multilingual WordPress Site</a><ul></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-wordpress-multilingual-seo\">What is WordPress Multilingual SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Multilingual SEO is the art and science of optimizing your content so that it ranks well in related language searches. It includes technical factors and content strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use WordPress plugins to handle the technical SEO tasks and to manage translations.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-why-is-wordpress-multilingual-seo-important\">Why is WordPress Multilingual SEO Important?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress multilingual SEO is important because it ensures that:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Search engines know which variation of a page to display in a particular country or region.</li><li>Your WordPress content reaches its intended audience, growing your traffic and sales.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to learn more?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-youll-need-an-seo-plugin-and-a-translation-plugin\">You’ll Need an SEO Plugin and a Translation Plugin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First, we’re going to install 2 WordPress plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A good SEO plugin will make it much easier for you to improve your rankings in search results. And it’ll handle the complicated tasks for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll also need a translation plugin. This is because WordPress won&#8217;t create a multilingual website &#8220;out of the box.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install and Setup the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a> Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your first step is to download the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140989\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage.png 1260w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This WordPress SEO plugin is easy to use and you don&#8217;t need any coding knowledge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More than 3 million people are now using this plugin. It has thousands of 5-star ratings on WordPress.org and comes with one-on-one customer support.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can find instructions for installing and activating AIOSEO <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"\">in this guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-follow-the-aioseo-setup-wizard\">Follow the AIOSEO Setup Wizard</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>After activating the plugin, the AIOSEO Setup Wizard will automatically launch.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Wizard will walk you through 4 easy steps. These include adding your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-social-media-profiles-to-your-wordpress-sites-schema/\">social media profile links</a> and website contact information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can leave the default settings as they are for now. Later in this article, we’ll discuss some simple tweaks you can make.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Great! You&#8217;re ready for the next steps now.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-2-install-and-setup-the-wpml-translation-plugin\">Step 2: Install and Setup the WPML Translation Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend the WPML translation plugin. It’s highly rated and fully compatible with AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After installing and activating your WPML plugin you&#8217;re ready to set it up.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-launch-the-wpml-plugin-wizard\">Launch the WPML Plugin Wizard</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In the left-hand navigation column of your WordPress editor, go to <strong>WPML » Setup</strong>. This will open the setup wizard. Just follow the wizard’s prompts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We think you may have some questions about Steps 2 and 6 of the wizard, so we’ve added some information on these below.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-url-structure\">URL Structure</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In Step 2 of the wizard, stick with the default option unless you’re planning on using a separate domain name (or sub-domain) for your translated content.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"619\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-1024x619.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140990\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-1024x619.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-300x181.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-768x464.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-600x363.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-99x60.png 99w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format-149x90.png 149w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-setup-url-format.png 1249w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The default option creates a separate directory (or folder) for each language. (This folder is also referred to as a sub-folder or sub-directory.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This URL structure makes it easier for search engines to find your translated content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-optional-components-to-download\">Optional Components to Download</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In Step 6 of the wizard, tick the box for String Translation. (This allows WPML to translate your SEO metadata.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’re using WooCommerce, go ahead and tick the box for the WooCommerce Multilingual &amp; Multicurrency Plugin. This plugin will make sure that the right currencies and payment gateways are displayed in your translated content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Have more questions? Check out the <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">WMPL setup guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay, now you&#8217;ve got your 2 plugins set up. And you’re ready to move on to the next steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-wordpress-multilingual-seo-foundations\">WordPress Multilingual SEO Foundations</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In this section, we’ll discuss some translation decisions you’ll need to make. And we’ll explain how you can use the AIOSEO plugin to optimize your translated content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-translation-considerations\">Translation Considerations</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You may be wondering, “Should I translate my whole site or just a few pages? And does it make a difference for SEO?”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This choice could, in fact, impact your SEO. Here’s why.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you only translate a few pages, then you only have a few opportunities to rank in foreign language searches. The more pages, the more opportunities to rank.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, realize that internal linking is a big SEO factor. For this to work on a multilingual site, you need to have enough content so that you can add links to related pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend translating your entire site. This will provide your site visitors with a better user experience (UX), which is also a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/seo-ranking-factors/#seorank7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">ranking factor</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-manual-translation-or-automatic-translation\">Manual Translation or Automatic Translation?</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You might also be wondering whether to hire a professional translator or use translation software like Google Translate.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s some information that can help you make that decision.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, realize that WPML gives you the option to get an automatic translation of your whole site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can choose between:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Google Translate</li><li>DeepL, or,</li><li>Microsoft Azure Translator.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This is definitely the most cost-effective option. (The plugin provides enough translation “credits” to cover most mid-sized sites.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But software-based translation (also called “machine translation”) is often inaccurate. And even when it is accurate, it can create passages that sound awkward to native speakers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So how can you get cheap automatic translations that don&#8217;t sound clunky?</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>First, start with simple content: Using plain language will make the translation process easier for humans and software.</li><li>Next, get a review: WPML offers <a href=\"https://wpml.org/translation-reviewer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">translation reviewers</a>. These translators will check your software-translated content. They’ll fix any errors, and polish it up. And they&#8217;re all experts in using the WPML plugin.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"368\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-1024x368.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140991\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-1024x368.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-300x108.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-768x276.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-600x215.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-167x60.png 167w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers-251x90.png 251w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-translator-reviewers.png 1301w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption><em>WPML has a directory of translation reviewers for you to pick from.</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For languages that use a different alphabet (like Chinese, Japanese, and Russian), we recommend using a professional translator. You can hire translation services right from the WPML plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-translate-all-seo-text\">Translate All SEO text</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s easy to overlook translating the following search engine optimization factors even though they are incredibly important for ranking:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/post-slug/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">Post Slugs</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/adding-breadcrumbs-to-your-site-using-the-aioseo-breadcrumbs-block/\">Breadcrumb navigation</a></li><li>Title tags</li><li>Meta descriptions</li><li>Image and video alt text</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>WPML can translate these bits of text automatically. But you may benefit from having a translation reviewer check them too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Things to look out for include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Slug translations that aren’t meaningful.</li><li>Title tags and meta descriptions that aren’t compelling or go over the recommended character count.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we’ve covered translation considerations, let’s move on to foundational SEO matters.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-social-media-international-considerations\">Social Media: International Considerations</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Be sure to add all your social media profile links to AIOSEO. Go to <strong>AIOSEO » Social Networks</strong> to do this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re using social media platforms like Qzone or Xing that are popular overseas and not listed in AIOSEO, simply add those profile URLs in the space at the bottom.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"974\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140992\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles.png 974w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles-300x263.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles-768x673.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles-600x526.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles-68x60.png 68w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-social-media-additional-profiles-103x90.png 103w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You may already know that Facebook provides country-specific pages. For example, Facebook.fr targets France. With AIOSEO, you can easily customize how your content will appear when shared on Facebook and Twitter. (See the instructions for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/configuring-the-facebook-settings-for-your-content/\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> and for<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/beginners-guide-to-social-networks-settings-for-twitter/\"> Twitter</a>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-search-engine-webmaster-tools\">Search Engine Webmaster Tools</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For each country you’re targeting, find out which search engines have a significant market share.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>In China, Baidu has around 60% market share.</li><li>In the Russian Federation, Yandex has about a 52% market share. [Source: Statscounter]</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are targeting China or Russia, or areas where these search engines are popular, we recommend you connect to and use the webmaster tools for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/baidu-webmaster-tools-verification/\">Baidu</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-verify-your-site-with-yandex-webmaster-tools/\" title=\"\">Yandex</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to <strong>AIOSEO » General settings » Webmaster Tools</strong> to do this.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"321\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-1024x321.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140993\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-1024x321.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-300x94.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-768x241.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-600x188.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-190x60.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools-287x90.png 287w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-webmaster-tools.png 1209w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you haven&#8217;t done so already, use the AIOSEO Webmaster Tools to verify your site with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-verify-your-site-with-google-search-console/\">Google Search Console</a> and<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-verify-your-site-with-bing-webmaster-tools/\"> Bing</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-sitemaps-keeping-search-engines-informed\">Sitemaps: Keeping Search Engines Informed</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Sitemaps, which are lists of your content URLs, are important for SEO. Search engines don’t need a sitemap to find your content. But sitemaps significantly speed up this process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve probably guessed that your translated content needs to be added to your sitemap. But don’t worry: this is all handled for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The AIOSEO plugin automatically:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Generates sitemaps for you</li><li>Adds your translated pages to the sitemaps, and,</li><li>Informs search engines when you add new content or update existing content.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, AIOSEO generates these 3 types of sitemaps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>An <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-an-xml-sitemap/\">XML sitemap</a></li><li>An <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-an-rss-sitemap/\">RSS sitemap</a></li><li>And an <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/html-sitemap/\">HTML sitemap</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To see the settings for your sitemaps go to <strong>AIOSEO » Sitemaps</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"239\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-1024x239.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140994\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-1024x239.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-300x70.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-768x179.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-600x140.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-190x44.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps-386x90.png 386w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-sitemaps.png 1086w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-video-and-google-news-sitemaps\">Video and Google News Sitemaps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll notice in the image above that AIOSEO offers 2 more sitemaps. You can switch these on with a few clicks.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Video Sitemap (available with the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Pro version</a> of AIOSEO): If you have any video content on your site, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/#why-should-you-create-a-video-sitemap\">turn this sitemap on</a>. It will make your videos eligible to be displayed as rich snippets in search results.</li><li>News Sitemap: This sitemap will push your<a href=\"https://support.google.com/news/publisher-center/#topic=10630761\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"> journalism content</a> to google.com/news. You can turn this sitemap on with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/create-a-google-news-sitemap/\">one click</a>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-review-the-basics-on-page-seo\">Review the Basics: On-Page SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll want to make sure all your content has good &#8220;on-page SEO.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can think of on-page SEO as a checklist you need to run through before publishing an article.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The good news is the AIOSEO plugin will check your on-page SEO for you and tell you how to improve it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s see how it works.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Open your WordPress editor and scroll to the bottom of a post. You&#8217;ll see a section at the bottom: <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong>. This is where you&#8217;ll find the plugin&#8217;s recommendations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this example below, AIOSEO shows a preview of how our article will display in search. And we can see that our post title for an article is within the recommended length.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"744\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-1024x744.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140995\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-1024x744.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-300x218.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-768x558.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-600x436.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-83x60.png 83w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length-124x90.png 124w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-settings-post-title-length.png 1111w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you scroll down further in the AIOSEO settings you’ll see a similar field for your meta description.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"1002\" height=\"398\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140996\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example.png 1002w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example-300x119.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example-768x305.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example-600x238.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example-151x60.png 151w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-meta-description-length-example-227x90.png 227w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Be aware that the translated versions of your title tags and meta descriptions may wind up over the recommended length. So be sure to review these on each piece of translated content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We like the idea of using a WPML translation reviewer to check and revise these since you want the tags to also provide searchers with a compelling reason to click through.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re new to on-page SEO, don’t fret.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Read this <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/on-page-seo-in-wordpress-your-complete-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">simple guide</a> for beginners.</li><li>Learn how to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/image-seo-optimize-images-for-search-engines/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">make your images SEO-friendly</a>.</li><li>And learn how to use the AIOSEO Schema feature <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/configuring-the-schema-settings-in-all-in-one-seo/\">here</a>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These factors will significantly improve how your content displays in search engine results pages (SERPs) and they can increase click-throughs to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-what-about-hreflang-tags\">What About hreflang Tags?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have read that hreflang tags are essential for multilingual SEO. That’s true. But don&#8217;t worry. WPML adds hreflang tags for you!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hreflang tags are bits of HTML code that <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/specialty/international/localized-versions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">tell search engines</a> that your site has content in different languages. And they help search engines figure out which variation of a page to show a searcher.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Curious to know more? Here are some things that hreflang can do:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Searchers in Argentina can see your Spanish-language pages created for their local dialect.</li><li>Users in Great Britain will see your pages in British English.</li><li>French speakers in the Boston area can see your content in French that refers to local places.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-1024x394.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140997\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-1024x394.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-300x116.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-768x296.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-600x231.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-156x60.jpg 156w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage-234x90.jpg 234w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/yelp-french-homepage.jpg 1384w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption><em>Image above: We accessed this French-language yelp.fr page from Boston. The page redirected us to yelp.fr/boston which provides reviews of local businesses. This is an example of translation combined with <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wordpress-geolocation-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">geolocation</a>.</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hreflang will also help Google understand how your translated pages relate to one another.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, Google will not think you’re creating duplicate content. (In SEO, some types of duplicate content can get your site penalized in ranking.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, let’s look at your role as a content creator.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-optimizing-content-for-multilingual-seo\">Optimizing Content for Multilingual SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You may be wondering whether you need to change anything about your content process now that you’re publishing in other languages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few things you’ll want to keep in mind.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-get-to-know-your-competitors\">Get to Know Your Competitors</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You already know who your competitors are in your home country. Now you need to find out who your competitors are in the new market you&#8217;re targeting.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve identified them, read some of their articles. How are they using content to attract visitors? Can you tell?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Are they entertaining people? Are they providing “how-to” tips? Helping people compare products?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What do they do well? What can you do better?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve collected some notes on your competitors you’re ready to reconsider keyword research.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-keyword-research-a-new-challenge\">Keyword Research: A New Challenge</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As you probably know, keyword research is the starting point for a successful content strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have pages on your WordPress website that rank well for the keywords you targeted. But translating those pages doesn’t mean they’ll rank in foreign language searches.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is because the search terms that people use vary across languages and regions. Also, the websites you need to beat now aren’t the same ones you competed against in your native language.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this reason, you’ll need to do keyword research in the targeted language(s). Your research may lead you to revise translated content to target different keywords. You might also decide to create multilingual content from scratch to target a new set of keywords.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In either case, a native speaker who’s familiar with SEO can be a big help.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(New to keyword research? Check out this great <a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/how-to-easily-find-the-best-keywords/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">beginner’s guide</a>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-localization-adapt-your-content\">Localization: Adapt Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Adapting your content to your target audience can make a big difference in SEO. Here are a few ways to get started.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you translate your content, look for country-based references. These might be mentions of holidays, popular foods, or places. Consider changing those references to reflect the location and culture you&#8217;re targeting.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Small business owners can adapt their <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/seedprod\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">landing pages</a> to address local problems. The pest control company Rentokil is a good example of this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They have a different landing page for each country they serve. And each country page displays a different list of “top pests.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a great example of using local information to show you understand and can solve searchers’ problems.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"487\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-1024x487.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140998\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-1024x487.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-300x143.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-768x365.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-600x285.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-126x60.jpg 126w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page-189x90.jpg 189w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/rentokill-finnish-page.jpg 1303w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption><em>Above: Rentokil’s Finnish landing page highlights in red the country’s top pests: &#8220;torakat&#8221; (cockroaches) and &#8220;Muurahaiset&#8221; (ants).</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, the more helpful (and relevant) your page is to a viewer, the more readers and inbound links you’ll get. Search engines will reward that and you’ll see improvements in your rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-link-building-a-powerful-seo-tactic\">Link-Building: A Powerful SEO Tactic</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding links to your content is one of the most powerful SEO actions you can take. Getting other websites to link to you can make a big difference too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to overlook links when planning your multilingual content though.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Internal linking</strong>: For your translated articles, make sure that the internal links go to pages in the same language.</li><li><strong>External linking</strong>: Find authoritative websites in your target language to link to. These should be trustworthy sources of information that provide value to your readers.</li><li><strong>Backlinks</strong>: Identify quality sites that you can guest post for in your targeted language(s). Then make sure to include a link to your website in that article.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO’s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-link-assistant-to-optimize-your-internal-linking-strategy/\">Link Assistant</a> will be your new best friend when it comes to managing <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-guide/\">link-building</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>It tracks all the links in your content.</li><li>It identifies “orphaned posts.” (These are posts that have no links from your other content.)</li><li>It recommends specific internal links for you to add. And you can do this with a click. You don’t even have to open the post.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This tool is a big time-saver. Once a month, sit down with a cup of coffee and Link Assistant and build some new links. It’ll be fun and you’ll start seeing results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"583\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1024x583.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-141012\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-1024x583.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-300x171.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-768x437.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-600x341.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-105x60.png 105w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard-158x90.png 158w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-link-assistant-dashboard.png 1220w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-review-your-404-page\">Review Your 404 Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Users who click on broken links to your site will see a &#8220;404&#8221; page. (That number refers to a technical error code.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Many site owners include a message and helpful links on their 404 page. This changes your 404 page from a dead-end into a useful resource.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example from Helpscout.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-1024x462.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-141001\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-1024x462.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-300x135.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-768x347.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-600x271.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-133x60.jpg 133w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page-199x90.jpg 199w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/helpscout-404-page.jpg 1427w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Don’t forget to check the automatic translation of your 404 page. (Remember: you can use WPML to get a translation reviewer to polish it.)</li><li>Make sure the translated 404 page links only to other translated pages.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This can help reduce your bounce rate and help readers find useful content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve now seen how your approach to keyword research, link-building, and localization will change with multilingual SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, a good SEO strategy will always include content factors as well as technical details.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-faqs-on-wordpress-multilingual-seo\">FAQs on WordPress Multilingual SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Below we’ve answered some common questions we get about WordPress multilingual SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-whats-a-language-switcher\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What’s a language switcher?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>A language switcher is a visual icon that allows website visitors to change their language preferences. The switcher usually appears as a flag icon next to the name of the language.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"130\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-1024x130.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-141003\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-1024x130.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-300x38.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-768x98.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-600x76.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-190x24.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher-709x90.png 709w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/wpml-language-switcher.png 1110w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Language switchers are often at the top of a homepage, in the footer, or next to a search field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The WPML WordPress multilingual plugin provides a customizable language switcher.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-doe-aioseo-integrate-with-other-translation-plugins\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Doe AIOSEO integrate with other translation plugins?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Yes, AIOSEO integrates with all translation plugins through its Translation API. You can think of the API, or “application programming interface,” as a pipe that allows translation plugins to access your SEO data. Getting metadata and off-page text like slugs, translated, is essential for multilingual SEO.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-bonus-tips-for-growing-your-multilingual-wordpress-site\">Bonus Tips for Growing Your Multilingual WordPress Site</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Great, so you&#8217;ve got 2 plugins that will handle the technical side of multilingual SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve covered how to get quality translations and how to find topics to write on. And you&#8217;ve seen how you can increase your rankings in SERPs (search engine results pages).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few more tips to help you get traction.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-use-multilingual-forms\">Use Multilingual Forms</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend (and use) the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">WPForms plugin</a> which is <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-wpml-multilingual-site-and-form-translation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">compatible with WPML</a>. So you can get automatic translations of your forms right inside WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WPForms is <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/the-ultimate-guide-to-wordpress-and-gdpr-compliance-everything-you-need-to-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">GDPR-friendly, too</a>. That’s important if you target searchers in the European Union.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-convert-and-monetize-your-international-traffic\">Convert and Monetize Your International Traffic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"http://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">OptinMonster</a> makes it easy to create cool marketing pop-ups, floating announcement bars, gamified wheels, and much more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can even target users based on their location. This is especially important for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/case-study-libratone-grew-list-400-percent-with-geotargeting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">multilingual e-commerce stores</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>OptinMonster is also compatible with WPML. (Grab some <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/s-to-increase-subscribers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">lead magnet ideas here</a>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-find-out-whats-working-and-do-more-of-it\">Find out What’s Working and Do More of it</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The MonsterInsights plugin connects with Google Analytics and provides easy-to-understand displays of important results like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/make-money-online/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">Revenue</a> trends and conversion rates</li><li>Which content is most popular in different countries</li><li>How AIOSEO’s on-page SEO score impacts your traffic</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And just like WPForms, MonsterInsights is GDPR-compliant for targeting the EU.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-keep-moving-forward-with-seo\">Keep Moving Forward With SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you&#8217;ve learned how to do SEO for your WordPress multilingual site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, AIOSEO’s default settings work great. And the plugin will make suggestions for what to do next to improve your site’s ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you learn what multilingual SEO is and how important it is for growing your business internationally. We recommend exploring how to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">use FAQs to boost SEO</a>. Plus, learn how to improve your SEO <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-small-business-seo/\">without expert help</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/the-beginners-guide-to-wordpress-multilingual-seo/\">The Beginner’s Guide to WordPress Multilingual SEO</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://aioseo.com/the-beginners-guide-to-wordpress-multilingual-seo/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"6 Best WordPress Product Review Plugins in 2023\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:138:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-product-review-plugins/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-wordpress-product-review-plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-product-review-plugins/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 28 Nov 2022 14:49:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"best wordpress product review plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"wordpress review plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=137580\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:452:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress product review plugins for your website? Product reviews play a massive role in helping increase conversion rates and drive sales. In this article, we’ll show you the best product review plugins for WordPress.&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-product-review-plugins/\">6 Best WordPress Product Review Plugins in 2023</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22805:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress product review plugins for your website?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Product reviews play a massive role in helping increase conversion rates and drive sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you the best product review plugins for WordPress. Most of them are super easy to use so you can use them without expert help.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-5 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-a-product-review-plugin-and-why-do-you-need-one\">What is a Product Review Plugin (and Why Do You Need One)?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-6-reasons-why-product-reviews-are-important\">6 Reasons Why Product Reviews are Important</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-the-best-wordpress-product-review-plugins-expert-picks\">The Best WordPress Product Review Plugins: Expert Picks</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">1. All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-wp-forms\">2. WP Forms</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-wp-review-pro\">3. WP Review Pro</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-wp-business-reviews\">4. WP Business Reviews</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-5-wp-customer-reviews\">5. WP Customer Reviews</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-6-site-reviews\">6. Site Reviews</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-bonus-social-proof-tool-trustpulse\">Bonus Social Proof Tool: TrustPulse</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-the-best-product-review-plugins-for-wordpress-our-top-picks\">The Best WordPress Product Review Plugins: Our Top Picks</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-a-product-review-plugin-and-why-do-you-need-one\">What is a Product Review Plugin (and Why Do You Need One)?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For most online shoppers, product reviews are a critical element that helps them decide whether to buy a product.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where Product review plugins come in. They help you display customer reviews on your website. Some even output product review schema for Google’s rich snippets on search engine results pages (SERPs). This results in more clicks and traffic to your content or WooCommerce product pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-6-reasons-why-product-reviews-are-important\">6 Reasons Why Product Reviews are Important</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Product reviews are an essential ingredient to effective online marketing for many reasons. The primary ones include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Social proof</strong>: People buy from brands others trust. Particularly if you’re a small business, getting more online reviews is a great way to prove to prospective customers that you’re a legitimate business.</li><li><strong>Build trust</strong>: User reviews are a great way to build trust with your audience as they show your reliability and competence to deliver on your promises. The higher the number of reviews, the more users will trust your brand.</li><li><strong>Drive sales</strong>: Reviews encourage prospects to buy from you as they show that previous customers were satisfied with your product or service.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Encourage customer loyalty</strong>: The more customers interact with your brand, the more likely they are to become loyal. And reviews are a great way to foster that interaction.</li><li><strong>Boost SEO</strong>: The more users mention your brand and product, the more likely search engines are to rank your product pages higher. Plus, when you output review schema markup, it <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\" title=\"8 Proven Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates\">positively impacts your clickthrough rates</a> (CTR), which also impacts your rankings in search results.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the importance of product reviews can not be overstated.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, while WordPress makes it easy to add new posts and pages to your site, adding product reviews requires additional features only offered by WordPress product review plugins.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-the-best-wordpress-product-review-plugins-expert-picks\">The Best WordPress Product Review Plugins: Expert Picks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you run an online store, review website, or blog, reviews are an essential ingredient to growth. Here’s our expertly curated list of the best WordPress review plugins on the market.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">1. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is a powerful tool that can help you add review schema on your site, making it one of the best WordPress product review plugins.\" class=\"wp-image-95222\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is by far the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market. Over 3 million savvy marketers and website owners use the plugin to help boost their rankings and drive relevant site traffic. This is because AIOSEO has many powerful SEO features designed to help you optimize your website and to dominate the SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on installing AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">step-by-step installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our next-gen Schema Generator is one of the reasons AIOSEO makes it to the top of this list of the best WordPress product review plugins. This powerful tool makes it easy to add any type of schema to your posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For ecommerce merchants or bloggers who sell products on their blogs, the <strong>Product</strong> schema module within the Schema Generator is a game-changer.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"403\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-product-option.png\" alt=\"The Product schema module is a powerful part of our next-gen Schema Generator.\" class=\"wp-image-132387\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-product-option.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-product-option-300x173.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-product-option-600x345.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One reason is that it supports <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-merchant-center-and-how-you-can-use-it-to-drive-sales/\" title=\"What is Google Merchant Center (And How You Can Use It To Drive Sales)?\">Google Merchant Center</a> (GMC) listing schema, a tool that helps users output interactive rich snippets on SERPs.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While the GMC listing schema used to be exclusively for merchants with a GMC account, you can now access it through AIOSEO, even if you don’t have a GMC account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Users love our next-gen Schema Generator because it makes it easy for you to add reviews to your pages, blog posts, custom post types, or WooCommerce product pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"526\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-aioseo-reviews.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s next-gen Schema Generator makes it easy to add review schema to any page on your site.\" class=\"wp-image-139495\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-aioseo-reviews.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-aioseo-reviews-300x225.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-aioseo-reviews-600x450.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This leads to the reviews being displayed in <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-product-rich-snippets-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add Product Rich Snippets in WordPress (The Easiest Way)\">your product rich results on SERPs</a>. Because of this, your search results will be more prominent, drive more clicks and generate more sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for a WordPress product review plugin that also helps with search engine optimization, you won’t find a better plugin than AIOSEO. It’s an invaluable tool if you want to show reviews in Google search results and other search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $49.60/year. A free version is also available.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-2-wp-forms\">2. <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">WP Forms</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"435\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/best-wordpress-multisite-plugins-wpforms.png\" alt=\"WP Forms is a powerful form builder that also helps add reviews to your site.\" class=\"wp-image-128844\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/best-wordpress-multisite-plugins-wpforms.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/best-wordpress-multisite-plugins-wpforms-300x186.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/best-wordpress-multisite-plugins-wpforms-600x373.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">WPForms</a> is the best WordPress form builder plugin and has been downloaded over 5 million times. The plugin enables you to easily create professional-looking forms for your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides being a form builder, WP Forms also offers a super easy way to let your users and customers submit reviews on your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin has a customizable pre-made template to create review and feedback forms. You can choose over 20 form fields to collect the type of reviews and testimonials you want, as well as set review criteria. It also comes with rating fields, including a star rating, thumbs up, and smileys. This enables you to choose between different review systems for your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the post submissions addon, <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-allow-users-to-leave-a-review-on-your-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">adding user reviews</a> to your site with WP Forms is super easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Pro versions start at $49.50. A free version is also available.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-3-wp-review-pro\">3. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/mythemeshop-wp-reviews-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WP Review Pro\">WP Review Pro</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/mythemeshop-wp-reviews-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-review.png\" alt=\"WP Review Pro is one of the best WordPress product review plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-139498\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-review.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-review-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-review-600x355.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for a product review plugin to help display customer reviews on your website, then <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/mythemeshop-wp-reviews-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WP Review Pro\">WP Review Pro</a> is one of the best.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WP Review Pro is highly rated as a WordPress product review plugin because it gives you full control over your product reviews. The plugin features a library of pre-designed templates you can easily customize to suit your website’s design or WordPress theme. It also comes with different types of rating systems, like percentage, star rating, points, and more.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WP Review Pro also helps you compile and display reviews from third-party sources like Facebook Reviews, Google Reviews, Yelp, etc. If you run a local business, it even pulls reviews from platforms like Google Places, helping your business stand out.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It also allows you to create a custom review box to help you present important review and product information in a simplified style.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: $67/year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-4-wp-business-reviews\">4. <a href=\"https://wpbusinessreviews.com/ref/syedbalkhi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WP Business Reviews\">WP Business Reviews</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wpbusinessreviews.com/ref/syedbalkhi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"384\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-business-reviews.png\" alt=\"WP Business Reviews is another excellent option when looking for a WordPress product review plugin.\" class=\"wp-image-139499\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-business-reviews.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-business-reviews-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-business-reviews-600x329.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wpbusinessreviews.com/ref/syedbalkhi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WP Business Reviews\">WP Business Reviews</a> is a WordPress review plugin that aggregates reviews customers leave on review platforms like Google, Yelp, and others. Once you collect them, it enables you to display them on your website. And whenever new reviews come in, you get a notification.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part about WP Business Reviews is that it has many customization options. For example, you can choose to display your reviews as a widget. This allows you to place the reviews anywhere on your site, including the sidebar, footer, or header. You can also customize how they are laid out in columns and the background color.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another handy feature you’ll love is that the plugin allows you to filter out negative reviews by setting the minimum rating to display.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for a premium plugin that seamlessly integrates with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-page-builders/\" title=\"8 Best and Popular WordPress Page Builders Compared\">your favorite page builder</a> and makes adding product reviews to yours easy, this could be it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $99/year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-5-wp-customer-reviews\">5. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-customer-reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WP Customer Reviews\">WP Customer Reviews</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-customer-reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"312\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-reviews-pro.png\" alt=\"If you\'re looking for the best free WordPress product review plugin, WP Customer Reviews could be it.\" class=\"wp-image-139500\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-reviews-pro.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-reviews-pro-300x134.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-wp-reviews-pro-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-customer-reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WP Customer Reviews\">WP Customer Reviews</a> is one of the best free product review plugins for WordPress and has over 40,000 users. The plugin allows you to set up a specific page on your site to collect and display user reviews.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the plugin&#8217;s best features is it allows you to vet the reviews users submit on the front end. This gives you full control over the ones you display on your site. The plugin also allows you to turn an existing WordPress blog post into a product review, complete with review schema to boost your SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, WP Customer Reviews has anti-spam functionality to prevent your site from getting bombarded by harmful reviews from malicious agents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-6-site-reviews\">6. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/site-reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Site Reviews\">Site Reviews</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/site-reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"310\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-site-reviews.png\" alt=\"Site Reviews is another free plugin you can use to add reviews on your WordPress website.\" class=\"wp-image-139501\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-site-reviews.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-site-reviews-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-site-reviews-600x266.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/site-reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Site Reviews\">Site Reviews</a> is another free plugin you can use to add reviews on your WordPress website. The plugin allows you to easily collect customer reviews for your products or services.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin also comes with a user-friendly settings dashboard that allows you to control how you want to gather reviews and how to display them on your site. You can also customize the review form and where you display it. As for your reviews, you can display them using the included Gutenberg block or shortcodes for displaying specific reviews or creating custom review sections.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Site Reviews is one of the best review plugins on the WordPress.org repository because it <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-woocommerce-seo-plugins/\" title=\"7 Best WooCommerce SEO Plugins And Tools to Get More Traffic\">integrates directly with WooCommerce</a>. This makes it easy for customers to leave reviews on your WooCommerce store.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-bonus-social-proof-tool-trustpulse\">Bonus Social Proof Tool: <a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"TrustPulse\">TrustPulse</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-trustpulse.png\" alt=\"TrustPulse is a powerful social proof tool that can help you boost conversions.\" class=\"wp-image-139502\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-trustpulse.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-trustpulse-300x197.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/best-product-review-plugins-trustpulse-600x395.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"TrustPulse\">TrustPulse</a> is the best social proof tool for helping you build trust with your website visitors. As a result, you get a boost in conversions. The plugin does this by displaying live notifications of customer actions on your website, such as sales, reviews, and more. This encourages visitors to do the same.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another powerful feature of the plugin is that it allows you to customize your notification popups. You can edit everything from the message title to the images to be displayed. Plus, you can also change the design of the notifications to only display customer reviews. The best part is the plugin automatically detects the name of customers who leave their reviews and adds them to the notification popups.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-the-best-product-review-plugins-for-wordpress-our-top-picks\">The Best WordPress Product Review Plugins: Our Top Picks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for the best WordPress product review plugin for SEO, then <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is it. Not only does it enable you to output product review schema, but the plugin comes with all the tools you need to rank your sites and drive traffic. Plus, it’s super easy to use for both beginners and experts alike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you’re looking for a plugin that helps you display customer reviews on your site, we recommend <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/mythemeshop-wp-reviews-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">WP Reviews Pro</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you find the best WordPress product review plugin for your site. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/\" title=\"7 Best WordPress FAQ Plugins in 2022\">best FAQ plugins for WordPress</a> and our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" title=\"Ultimate WordPress SEO Guide: Optimize Your Site in 2022\">ultimate guide to WordPress SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-product-review-plugins/\">6 Best WordPress Product Review Plugins in 2023</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-product-review-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO and Get More Traffic\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:196:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 24 Nov 2022 15:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"best faq plugin for wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"what is a faq block\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"wordpress faq block\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=135905\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:487:\"<p>Do you want to learn how to use the WordPress FAQ block to boost your SEO? WordPress FAQ blocks can increase your website traffic and click-through rates. They can even help you beat your competitors. In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO and Get More Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30609:\"<p>Do you want to learn how to use the WordPress FAQ block to boost your SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress FAQ blocks can increase your website traffic and click-through rates. They can even help you beat your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn how to optimize WordPress FAQ blocks and use them strategically to drive real results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What you&#8217;ll need</strong>: The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"\">All in One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-6 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-use-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Why Use a WordPress FAQ Block?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install and Activate the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-add-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-a-post\">Step 2: Learn How to Add an FAQ Block in WordPress</a><ul></ul></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-faq-content-tips\">FAQ Content Tips</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-use-faq-blocks-to-supercharge-your-traffic\">How to Use FAQ Blocks to Supercharge Your Traffic</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-use-faqs-to-steal-your-competitors-traffic\">Use FAQs to &#8216;Steal&#8217; Your Competitor’s Traffic</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-aim-to-rank-in-people-also-ask-boxes\">Aim to Appear in the &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes</a><ul></ul></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-use-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Why Use a WordPress FAQ Block?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Using FAQ blocks in WordPress is a proven way to <strong>increase traffic and CTRs</strong> (click-through rates).</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Using a plugin like AIOSEO is an easy way to optimize your Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) for search engines.</li><li>The plugin adds code called &#8220;FAQ Schema markup.&#8221;&nbsp;</li><li>Now your FAQs can appear in search engine results.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example using the search term &#8220;things to do in cancun&#8221;.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"469\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-1024x469.jpg\" alt=\"faq serp example\" class=\"wp-image-135912\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-1024x469.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-300x137.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-768x352.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-600x275.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-131x60.jpg 131w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-196x90.jpg 196w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example.jpg 1386w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>See how the Trip Advisor article stands out because it includes those two FAQs?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it gets better. You can even include<em> links</em> in your FAQs. Take a look at what happens when we click on one of the FAQs in the example: It expands to reveal the answer, which contains 6 links.<br><br>So, this one search result provides 7 links for a single article.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"700\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-1024x700.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135914\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-1024x700.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-300x205.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-768x525.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-600x410.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-88x60.jpg 88w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-132x90.jpg 132w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example.jpg 1261w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to unlock these kind of results with WordPress FAQ blocks?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install and Activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First, head over to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"\">AIOSEO</a> to get their SEO plugin.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135917\" width=\"706\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage.png 1260w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is an easy-to-use WordPress plugin popular with small businesses and bloggers. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Right now, more than 3 million WordPress site owners are using AIOSEO. And a big majority of reviewers have given it a 5-star rating on WordPress.org.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best features of this plugin is the AIOSEO FAQ block. This block will add the SEO code that your FAQs need.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After downloading the plugin from AIOSEO, open your WordPress editor and go to <strong>Plugins » Add New</strong>. Then upload the zip file of the plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Have questions? Follow the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installation-instructions-for-wordpress-com-users/\" title=\"\">instructions here</a> to install and activate it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-2-add-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-a-post\">Step 2: Learn How to Add an FAQ Block in WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you’ve installed and activated the AIOSEO plugin, you’re ready to create some FAQs.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Open your WordPress block editor (also called the Gutenberg editor).</li><li>On a post or page, click the “add block” icon (the black plus sign).&nbsp;</li><li>In the search field of the pop-up window, type in &#8220;AIOSEO.&#8221; The <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> option will appear alongside other helpful AIOSEO blocks. Click on&nbsp;<strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"550\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-1024x550.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135923\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-1024x550.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-768x412.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-600x322.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-112x60.png 112w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-168x90.png 168w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block.png 1440w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An FAQ block will appear on your page with two prompts:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Write a question . . .&nbsp;</li><li>Write an answer . . .&nbsp;</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"879\" height=\"327\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135925\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts.png 879w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-300x112.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-768x286.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-600x223.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-161x60.png 161w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-242x90.png 242w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Go ahead and type in your FAQ question and your answer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then, repeat the process to add another FAQ to your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That was easy, wasn’t it?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-3-optional-choose-faq-design-and-display-options\">Step 3 (Optional): Choose FAQ Design and Display Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block offers several design and display options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To view these options, place your cursor anywhere in an FAQ block on your post or page.&nbsp;The options will now display under <strong>Block</strong> in the right-hand sidebar menu.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scroll down that right-hand column to see all the options:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"673\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-1024x673.png\" alt=\"aioseo wordpress faq block design options\" class=\"wp-image-136277\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-1024x673.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-300x197.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-768x505.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-600x395.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options.png 1326w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The options include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Title wrapper</strong>: Choose which heading tag you want to use for the FAQ questions, such as h2, h3, h4.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Visibility</strong>: By default, this is set to “Display Block.” This toggle gives you the option to hide the FAQ block from the front end of your site. That means that visitors will no longer be able to see the FAQ. Search engines will continue to see it because AIOSEO will still output the schema markup.</li><li><strong>Color</strong>: You can alter your FAQ text color or add a background color.</li><li><strong>Dimensions</strong>: You can use this to create more space around your FAQ content or to alter the margin size.</li><li><strong>Typography</strong>: Here you can alter the font size and line height.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As you scroll down the right-hand navigation, you’ll see some <strong>Advanced</strong> options too:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>HTML anchor</strong>: This is an easy way to create an HTML anchor link. You can use the URL to link to a specific area of your FAQ.</li><li><strong>Additional CSS class(es): </strong>Here&#8217;s where you would paste CSS code to customize your FAQ&#8217;s appearance.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"620\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-1024x620.png\" alt=\"aioseo advanced faq block options\" class=\"wp-image-136276\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-1024x620.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-300x182.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-768x465.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-600x363.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options.png 1430w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-4-review-googles-guidelines-for-faqs\">Step 4: Review Google’s Guidelines for FAQs</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We mentioned earlier that the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block adds FAQ Schema markup to FAQs. This markup is a type of code that search engines need to identify FAQ content so they can display it in a special way.<br><br>It’s worth noting that Google has some guidelines for FAQ content.<br><br>For example, your FAQs should:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Include one single answer.</li><li>Have more than one question-and-answer pair. (Otherwise you&#8217;d use a different Schema markup.)</li><li>Not have an option for site visitors to submit their own answers to your question.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can read Google’s guidelines <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/structured-data/faqpage#guidelines\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay! Now you know how to add FAQ blocks in WordPress and optimize them for search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s talk about some content factors that can put you ahead of the game.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-faq-content-tips\">FAQ Content Tips</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep these tips and ideas in mind when planning your FAQs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-faq-pages-and-sections\">FAQs: Where to Put Them?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can create one or more FAQ pages on your site. These are resource pages that have nothing but FAQs on them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a popular option with businesses. For example, software companies often have one or more FAQ pages in the customer support area of their website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, some sites include a navigation (or sub-navigation) item labeled “FAQ.” This can improve user experience by helping site visitors find your FAQ.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also publish FAQs on pages that feature other content. For example, you can add FAQs to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Product pages</li><li>Blog posts&nbsp;</li><li>Event pages</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-answer-faqs-well\">How to Answer FAQs Well</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your answers need to be well-written if they’re going to rank. That&#8217;s because content quality is a big ranking factor.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Follow these principles and you’ll be creating quality FAQs in no time:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Be clear and use simple language</li><li>Be concise</li><li>Don’t change the subject</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>That last bit is important. We&#8217;ve all known that person who goes on and on when you ask them a simple question.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t be that person.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure to answer the question in the first sentence. After the first sentence, add details if they&#8217;re relevant to the question.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your readers will thank you!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-find-faqs-to-answer\">How to Come Up With FAQs to Answer</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You already know many of the questions site visitors have about your content or products.<br><br>Here are some ways to discover more FAQs to answer:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Social media</strong>: check your social media accounts for questions left by visitors.</li><li><strong>Reviews</strong>: Check online reviews for questions or customer pain points.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Blog post comments</strong>: Scan these to discover questions that are common.</li><li><strong>Support and sales teams</strong>: Meet with your team to discover repeat questions.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s kick things up a notch. Ready?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;re going to learn how to create FAQs that help you gain market share from competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-use-faq-blocks-to-supercharge-your-traffic\">How to Use FAQ Blocks to Supercharge Your Traffic</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to unlock the full power of FAQs, it’s not enough to optimize them for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some insider tactics that the best (and most expensive!) content marketers use.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-use-faqs-to-steal-your-competitors-traffic\">Use FAQs to &#8216;Steal&#8217; Your Competitor’s Traffic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know you can use FAQs to get traffic and sales from your competitors&#8217; prospects?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You do this by answering questions searchers are asking about those competitors. These questions can be about hours, prices, guarantees, refunds, services, products, features, and so on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s look at an example of how this works.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine that DocuSign is a competitor of yours. You want to see what ranks on page 1 for the search term (keyword)&nbsp;“does DocuSign charge per user?” (That&#8217;s a question a prospect might have before purchasing DocuSign.)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>First, open up the Chrome browser in Incognito mode. (If you&#8217;re using a different browser, use their version of privacy/incognito mode.)&nbsp;</li><li>Search for&nbsp;“does DocuSign charge per user?”&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Page 1 of search engine result pages (SERPs) for that keyword shows us something interesting.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SignNow, which is a competitor to DocuSign, has answered this FAQ. And it’s currently ranking on page 1 of search results for that keyword.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-1024x572.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135953\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-1024x572.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-768x429.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-600x335.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-107x60.png 107w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-161x90.png 161w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example.png 1137w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So now, people searching for details on DocuSign&#8217;s pricing can find out about SignNow. And when they click through to SignNow, they’ll see it’s cheaper. Clever!</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-be-objective-and-accurate\">Build Trust: Be Objective and Accurate</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>When answering FAQs on your competitors, it’s important to be accurate. Say good things about their product where warranted. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The more you sound like a trustworthy third party in your competitor FAQs, the more likely your answers will rank well. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please note that this doesn&#8217;t mean you are trying to trick Google. Search engines know the source of any given FAQ. The goal here is to meet Google&#8217;s standards for quality. Quality is always a huge ranking factor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t forget to say why your product might be a better alternative. For example, if you offer a free feature that your competitor charges for, say so.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You don’t always need to highlight your benefits in the FAQ answer itself though. Use your judgement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, you’re using the FAQ about your competitor to get click-throughs to your website. Once the visitors are on your web page, they can read more about how your products compare.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tip: Include one or more internal links in the answers where relevant or practical. But don’t force a link into an answer if you have no good options for one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-aim-to-rank-in-people-also-ask-boxes\">Aim to Appear in the &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let&#8217;s look at how you can get your FAQs to land in People Also Ask boxes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-what-are-people-also-ask-boxes\">What are &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes?</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Google often (but not always) displays a section on page 1 of search results called “People Also Ask&#8221; (PAA). These are common questions people have about the related search term.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As such, they reveal important information about search intent.<br><br>To see an example of PAA let&#8217;s open Chrome Incognito. Type in the same search term as before (“does DocuSign charge per user?”).<br><br>Now scroll down a bit to find the “People Also Ask” questions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-1024x485.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135957\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example.png 1229w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you click on each question, its answer will appear. After clicking on a question, additional &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; questions will appear at the bottom of the box.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s look at the first PAA question: &#8220;How much does it cost to add a user to DocuSign?&#8221; </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on the question reveals it&#8217;s been answered by PandaDoc, another DocuSign competitor!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"977\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135961\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1.png 977w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-300x246.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-768x629.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-600x491.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-73x60.png 73w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-110x90.png 110w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-create-faqs\">Steps to Get Your FAQs in PAA Boxes</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To boost the chances that some of your FAQs will appear in a PAA box, we recommend taking these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>For each article you write, identify the main topic first. In SEO, this is called a keyword, a search term, or a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/using-the-focus-keyphrase-to-analyze-your-content/\" title=\"Using the Focus Keyphrase to Analyze Your Content\">focus keyphrase</a>. (Follow <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-properly-use-focus-keyphrase-in-wordpress-beginners-guide/\" title=\"\">these easy instructions</a>.) This is good SEO practice for every article. But it&#8217;s also going to help you find relevant PAA to answer. This is because PAA questions appear in relation to a search term.</li><li>For each page or post you create, search in Chrome Incognito for your article&#8217;s main keyword.</li><li>Explore the People Also Ask questions that appear.&nbsp;</li><li>Choose some PAA questions to answer in your article. (Not all PAA questions will be relevant to your keyword. Use your judgment when choosing which ones to answer.)&nbsp;</li><li>Add your FAQs to your page.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-do-faqs-need-schema-markup-to-land-in-paa-boxes\">Do FAQs Need Schema Markup to Land in PAA Boxes?</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>At this point, we want share some nuanced information. Your FAQs don&#8217;t need FAQ Schema markup applied to them in order to be selected by Google to appear in a PAA box.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The quality of your answer and your web page, and the nature of the competition, are the biggest ranking factors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, we recommend you always optimize your FAQs with Schema markup so that you run a higher chance of getting your FAQs displayed, along with your title and description, in regular search results. (See the &#8220;things to do in cancun&#8221; example at the beginning of this article.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Great, we&#8217;ve covered some ideas for FAQ content and some strategic moves that can make a significant difference in your click-through rates (CTRs).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember: to rank for FAQs, be concise and clear in your answers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To the degree that you help the reader, Google, Bing, Yandex, and other search engines will reward you.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-have-more-questions-about-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Have More Questions About the WordPress FAQ Block?</h2>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-an-faq-rich-snippet\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What is an FAQ rich snippet? </h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>An FAQ rich snippet (or &#8220;FAQ rich result&#8221;) refers to the way Google displays some FAQs in search results. To appear as a &#8220;rich snippet,&#8221; an FAQ must have FAQ schema markup added to it. In search results, FAQ rich snippets appear beneath an article&#8217;s title and description. They appear in accordion format (clicking on a question reveals the answer). FAQ rich snippets can include links in the answer area.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-move-my-wordpress-faq-block\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How Do I Move my WordPress FAQ Block?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>To move your WordPress FAQ block, do the following: Place your cursor inside the FAQ block. Then select the 6-dot “Drag“ icon to drag and drop the block where you want it. Or click the “Move up” or “Move down” arrow to move the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(If you don’t have any content below the FAQ, then the “Move down” arrow will appear grayed out.)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"941\" height=\"283\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-136316\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block.png 941w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-300x90.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-768x231.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-600x180.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-190x57.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-299x90.png 299w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-the-best-faq-plugin-for-wordpress\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What is the best FAQ plugin for WordPress?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>The <a href=\"http://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/\" title=\"\">best WordPress FAQ plugins</a> optimize your content for SEO. And they provide design options. Here are some recommendations:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin</li><li>FAQ by 10Web</li><li>Heroic WordPress FAQ Plugin (allows video embeds in answer sections)</li><li>Tribulant WordPress FAQ Plugin</li><li>Quick and Easy FAQs</li><li>Ultimate FAQ</li><li>Helpie FAQ (Helpie FAQ also includes WooCommerce and Elementor integrations)</li></ul>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-add-faqs-in-wordpress-without-a-plugin\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How do I add FAQs in WordPress without a plugin?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>To create an FAQ section in WordPress without using a plugin:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>First, navigate to the page or post in question.</li><li>Use an h2, h3, or h4 heading for your questions.</li><li>Add a paragraph block below each question for the answer.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>But remember, using a WordPress FAQ block plugin will optimize your FAQ for SEO. This ensures that your FAQs can display as rich snippets in search results. SEO-optimized FAQs are an important part of growing your site traffic.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-can-i-add-custom-schema-markup-to-the-aioseo-plugin\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Can I add custom FAQ Schema markup to the AIOSEO plugin?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Yes, you can add custom FAQ Schema markup to the AIOSEO plugin. For example, you could add the property <strong>reviewedBy</strong> if you use a subject matter expert to fact-check your authors’ FAQs. Follow these simple <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/creating-custom-schema-markup-with-all-in-one-seo/\">instructions</a> for adding your Schema markup in JSON-LD. You can <a href=\"http://​​​​​​​https://aioseo.com/docs/testing-your-schema-in-all-in-one-seo/\" title=\"validate your code\">validate your code</a> by clicking a button. And you can save the custom Schema as a template.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimized FAQ blocks can increase click-throughs and drive traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And you’ve seen how you can use them to grab market share from competitors.<br><br>We hope this article has helped you learn how to use FAQ blocks to boost SEO and get more traffic. Next, check out our tips on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-small-business-seo/\">boosting SEO without expert help</a>. And explore some easy ways to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\">increase your click-through rates</a> (CTRs.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO and Get More Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:1